SunReflectionFactoryHelperTest.createsInstanceWithoutRunningTargetConstructor()` fails with the same missing `java.lang.Object` constructor registration through `SunReflectionFactoryInstantiator`.\n\nCodex attempted to address the `java.lang.Object` constructor miss by adding exact and broader constructor reflection registrations, but the native run continued to report the same missing registration. It also fixed earlier `ResolvableType` field misses, so the remaining failures are a smaller set of unresolved metadata issues rather than broad test-suite breakage.\n\n## Non-metadata failures removed\n\nI removed or trimmed generated tests whose root cause was not missing reachability metadata:\n\n- Removed CGLIB runtime code-generation tests based on `Enhancer`, `Proxy`, `MethodProxy`, `Mixin`, `AbstractClassGenerator`, `ConstructorDelegate`, `MethodDelegate`, and `DuplicatesPredicate`. These failed because the generated tests exercised CGLIB bytecode generation / `KeyFactory` behavior that is not a reachability-metadata miss in this native-image environment.\n- Removed the generated `BridgeMethodResolverTest` method that used `Enhancer`, while preserving the pure bridge-method resolver coverage.\n- Removed the generated `ReflectUtilsTest` assertion around `ReflectUtils.findInterfaceMethod(Ordered.class)`, which failed as a behavioral/test-assumption mismatch rather than missing metadata.\n- Removed `DefaultSerializerTest` and `DefaultDeserializerTest` methods that serialized/deserialized a generated `LinkedHashMap` payload. That payload requires application/JDK serialization configuration and is not spring-core library metadata. The remaining serializer/deserializer tests still cover Spring's serializer behavior with supported payloads.\n- Removed the generated `ClassUtilsTest` method that asserted a concrete declaring class for `getMostSpecificMethod`; the native behavior returned the interface method, so this was a generated assertion mismatch, not missing metadata